sec.p:
The damping or altered elastic properties of the cantilever during the experiment, e.g. by a stiffening or softening of the spring constant caused by the adsorption of a molecule layer, result in the fact that the measured resonance frequency will not be exactly equal to the eigenfrequency of the cantilever, and therefore the mass derived from the frequency shift will be inaccurate. In a medium, the vibration of a cantilever is described by the model of a driven damped harmonic oscillator
