where m* = const(mc + ml) is the effective mass of the cantilever (for a rectangular cantilever the constant is 0.25). Especially in liquids, the mass of the comoved liquid ml adds significantly to the mass of the cantilever mc. The term γdxdt is the drag force due to damping, F cos (2πft) is the driving force executed by the piezo-oscillator, and k is the spring constant of the cantileverspring constantcantilever.
